    <h2>About Me</h2>
    <p>
        I was pretty confident about wanting to be a scientist of some kind since I was young. Fish were my favorite
        animals and I'd stare over the railings at every body of water searching for signs of life. 
        I also enjoyed catching crickets and other bugs and observing birds in my neighborhood. I'm trying to get better at herping as well. But in addition
        to touching grass, I also really enjoyed computers, learning typing from Mavis Beacon and playing
        Coolmath Games in the computer lab at school. Over a decade later, I'm still sticking with these two interests and trying to make
        a career out of them. I am a terminally online-outside hybrid! Hopefully this website is some indication
        I'm on the way to realizing my childhood dreams. 
    </p>
    <p>
        I also don't really want this website to just be a nicer looking version of my CV. I enjoy trying new things
        and pursuing my hobbies. I've been playing basketball in some capacity since I was a toddler, and I started reading about metaphysics
        and existentialist philosophy in college. I'm working on creating some comma-separated list of interests and implementing that throughout this site.
